Description: Round-topped limestone stela of Iufseneb divided into four registers: 1 - Two wedjat-eyes. 2 - Four rows of Hieroglyphic text. 3 - Three male and one female figure. 4 - Four female figures.
Bibliographic references: Hall 1912 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc., in the British Museum, Part 3. (pl.24)
